    <h2>
        Welcome to our hospotal</h2>
    <p>
        A <b>hospital</b> is a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health_care" 
            title="Health care">health care</a> institution providing
        <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient" title="Patient">patient</a> 
        treatment with specialized staff and equipment. The best-known type of hospital 
        is the general hospital, which has an
        <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emergency_department" 
            title="Emergency department">emergency department</a>. A district hospital 
        typically is the major health care facility in its region, with large numbers of 
        beds for <a class="mw-redirect" 
            href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intensive_care" title="Intensive care">
        intensive care</a> and long-term care. Specialised hospitals include
        <a class="mw-redirect" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trauma_centre" 
            title="Trauma centre">trauma centres</a>,
        <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rehabilitation_hospital" 
            title="Rehabilitation hospital">rehabilitation hospitals</a>,
        <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Children's_hospital" 
            title="Children's hospital">children&#39;s hospitals</a>, seniors&#39; (<a 
            class="mw-redirect" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geriatric" 
            title="Geriatric">geriatric</a>) hospitals, and hospitals for dealing with 
        specific medical needs such as <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychiatry" 
            title="Psychiatry">psychiatric</a> problems (see
        <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychiatric_hospital" 
            title="Psychiatric hospital">psychiatric hospital</a>), certain disease 
        categories. Specialised hospitals can help reduce <a class="mw-redirect" 
            href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health_care_costs" title="Health care costs">
        health care costs</a> compared to general hospitals. A
        <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teaching_hospital" 
            title="Teaching hospital">teaching hospital</a> combines assistance to 
        people with teaching to medical students and nurses. The medical facility 
        smaller than a hospital is generally called a
        <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinic" title="Clinic">clinic</a>. 
        Hospitals have a range of departments (e.g.,
        <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surgery" title="Surgery">surgery</a>, and
        <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urgent_care" title="Urgent care">urgent 
        care</a>) and specialist units such as
        <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cardiology" title="Cardiology">cardiology</a>. 
        Some hospitals will have <a class="mw-redirect" 
            href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Outpatient" title="Outpatient">outpatient 
        departments</a> and some will have chronic treatment units. Common support units 
        include a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hospital_pharmacy" 
            title="Hospital pharmacy">pharmacy</a>,
        <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathology" title="Pathology">pathology</a>, 
        and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radiology" title="Radiology">radiology</a>.</p>
